; NEW SLAB ATLAS (#426 soak-rev, Uma s1-slab-path-texture.md): `floor_slab.png` is a
; 512x128 = 16x4 cell atlas (32px tiles) = FOUR 4x4 variant-blocks side by side
; (variant v = cols [v*4 .. v*4+3]) — the SAME packed-variant layout as the cobble
; atlas, so S1YardChunk's block-variant scatter applies to slabs identically (no single
; repeated stamp down the processional spine = the anti-grid repeat-break, spec §3.2).
; Each variant is a distinct 384px ASHLAR source (irregular worn cut-stone pavers,
; foot-polished bright centers + sunk dirt-shadow edges, ZERO baked vegetation) down-
; sampled to 128px. Region size 32x32 = the game tile (was 16x16 over the old 64px
; sandstone). One paver renders ~2.5-3x the largest cobble at game zoom (spec §5.1
; scale step-up), no longer "too big / chunky blocky rectangles".
